HEADWORD: Sarcous
<hw>Sar"cous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sa`rx</grk>, <grk>sa`rkos</grk>, flesh.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Fleshy; -- applied to the minute structural elements, called
<xex>sarcous elements</xex>, or <xex>sarcous disks</xex>, of which
striated muscular fiber is composed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

